                    </form>
                </div>
                    <!-- this one is just in case the passwords don't match, in which case, the dissidents kill the character -->
                <div id="kill1">
                    <p>You can only assume the dissidents did not like your answers. They make eye-contact with one another briefly, exchange a subtle nod, and then blur into motion. One throws open the door of the van, while the other grabs you by the scruff of your neck. You struggle weakly, but even if you weren't drugged, the guy seems pretty strong, and not at all unfamiliar with throwing people out of moving vehicles.</p>
                    <p>Regardless, you do not do a very good job of defending yourself. You end up sailing out of the van before you know what has happened. You hit the pavement, hard, and tumble to stop. You've broken quite a few bones, and ruptured your spleen. Disoriented, drugged, and mortally injured, you quietly die in the ditch by the side of the road.</p>
                    <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg killedOff" role="button">Thanks for playing!</a>
                </div>
                <div id="intro6">
                    <p>You realize that you have lost track of time. As the van drives around, you know not where, you cannot begin to guess how much time has passed. You also seem unable to recount what you and these people have been talking about.</p>

                    <p>They tell you that members of Project Mayhem do not have names. A nihilistic secret society that shuns the idea of identity, possession, and glory. The man who first approached is to serve as your handler, something of a mentor figure as they continue to monitor your progress during your first two weeks. They call it your 'trial.'</p>
                    <p> Your handler will serve as your sole connection to Project Mayhem during the course of your trial. You are to follow his lead, and do as he says until your introductory period is finished.</p>
                    <form id="form4">
                        <a role="button" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" id="toIntro7" >He continues</a>
                    </form>
                </div>
                <div id="intro7">
                    <p>You can feel your wits returning to you, slowly but surely. The atmosphere remains relaxed. You reassess your location, and find the van seems on its way back to where you were picked up. It would appear that the interview is almost concluded.</p>
                    <p>Your handler begins enumerating the rules of the organization. There are only five.</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li>You do not ask questions about Project Mayhem.</li>
                        <li>You do not ask questions about Project Mayhem!</li>
                        <li>No Excuses</li>
                        <li>No Lies</li>
                        <li>You have to trust Tyler Durden.</li>
                    </ol>

                    <p>You think to ask who the hell Tyler Durden is, but think better of it, considering the first two rules. As the van slows, and then stops, your handler tells you that they will run your information the following day, and will be contacting you some time in the next week. Once you are cleared, Project Mayhem will destroy any personal information they have on you so that, in the event of infiltration, you and others won't be compromised.</p>
                     <a id="finish" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" role="button" >Finish initiation</a>
                </div>

                <div id="intro8">
                    <p>One of the unnamed members opens the door when the van has stopped, and you hop out, just where you got on. They drive off casually, without so much as a farewell.</p>
                    <p>The narcotic has been all but metabolized. You feel drained, and slightly nauseous, but otherwise unaffected. The hour has gotten quite late, and you head for your home. The interview lasted almost an hour exactly</p>
